result.execSummary:
The defendant Jordon W Reinke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Jordon W Reinke is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Jordon W Reinke was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Jordon W Reinke was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Jordon W Reinke was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

records.addlTxt: Defendant Jordon W Reinke in court.  Scott E. Niemi appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Right to counsel given - defendant proceeds w/o counsel.  Court accepts waiver of attorney for now.  DA makes recommendation with and without counseling.  Defendant enters a plea of no contest to 3 counts.  Court advises party of their rights, finds factual basis, accepts defendant's waiver of their rights, the plea made, and finds guilty.  Count 3 dismissed.  Defendant's parents make a statement.  Defendant apologizes.  Court orders Ct 1 - $250 + costs, Ct 2 and 4 - $20 + costs each.

Defendant Jordon W Reinke in court.  Scott E. Niemi appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Right to counsel given - defendant wishes to speak with an attorney.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for July 20, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
